name: 2-Methoxyethanol
Reason: 2-Methoxyethanol has a molecular weight slightly higher than ethanol due to the presence of a methoxy group. However, the methoxy group also increases the potential for hydrogen bonding due to the presence of an additional oxygen atom. Since ethanol already has hydrogen bonding, the additional oxygen atom allows for more hydrogen bond formation, which can further lower the melting point. Taking the effect of the methoxy group into consideration, we can predict a net decrease due to additional hydrogen bonding.
